					<div class="commentCopy"><div class="blocktag">Quote:</div><blockquote class="quote"><div>Originally Posted by <b>Shagbag</b><br />This is pathetic, not because it perpetuates the false belief that everything in a EULA is somehow legally binding, but because they somehow think you've missed out by failing to claim the £5 voucher. <br />
What exactly can I buy from Gamestation that will cost no more than £5 incl. p&amp;p?  I'd hazard a guess at nothing.  I can buy nothing from Gamestation for £5 incl. p&amp;p.  O NOES!  I missed out on this amazing offer!<br />
The 'stunt' is no more than an insult to the intelligence.</div></blockquote><br />
Erm little thing, this isn't a EULA, it's a shopping sites terms of sale, not a license agreement to buy from them.</div>
				</div>
